  "chapter": {
    "number": 17,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Prepares for Death"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“My spirit is broken; my days are extinguished;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the grave awaits me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely mockers surround me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my eyes must gaze at their rebellion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Give me, I pray, the pledge You demand.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who else will be my guarantor?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have closed their minds to understanding;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "therefore You will not exalt them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If a man denounces his friends for a price,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the eyes of his children will fail.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has made me a byword among the people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a man in whose face they spit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My eyes have grown dim with grief,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my whole body is but a shadow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The upright are appalled at this,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the innocent are stirred against the godless.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet a righteous one holds to his way,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the one with clean hands grows stronger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But come back and try again, all of you.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For I will not find a wise man among you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My days have passed; my plans are broken off—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even the desires of my heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They have turned night into day,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "making light seem near in the face of darkness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If I look for Sheol as my home,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if I spread out my bed in darkness,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and say to corruption, ‘You are my father,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to the worm, ‘My mother,’ or ‘My sister,’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "where then is my hope?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who can see any hope for me?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will it go down to the gates of Sheol?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will we go down together into the dust?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
